<doc id="988318" wikidata="Q772957" url="?curid=988318" title="Hyphaene">
<text>Hyphaene is a genus of palms native to Africa, Madagascar, the Middle East, and the Indian subcontinent.

The genus includes the Doum palm (&quot;H. thebaica&quot;). They are unusual among palms in having regular naturally branched trunks; most other palms are single-stemmed from the ground. In Swahili, it is called &quot;koma&quot;.

==Species==
* &quot;Hyphaene compressa&quot; - eastern Africa from Ethiopia to Mozambique
* &quot;Hyphaene coriacea&quot; - eastern Africa from South Africa; Madagascar; Juan de Nova Island
* &quot;Hyphaene dichotoma&quot; - India, Sri Lanka
* &quot;Hyphaene guineensis&quot; - western and central Africa from Liberia to Angola
* &quot;Hyphaene macrosperma&quot; - Benin
* &quot;Hyphaene petersiana&quot; - southern and eastern Africa from South Africa to Tanzania
* &quot;Hyphaene reptans&quot; - Somalia, Kenya, Yemen
* &quot;Hyphaene thebaica&quot; - northeastern, central and western Africa from Egypt to Somalia and west to Senegal and Mauritania; Middle East (Palestine, Israel, Saudi Arabia, Yemen)

